==Korean==
===Noun===
'''물개''' (''mulgae'') (''literally, "[[water]] [[dog]]"'')
# [[ear]]ed [[seal]], [[fur]] [[seal]], [[sea lion]] 
# [[otter]]

====Synonyms====
*[[바다사자]] (''bada-saja'') (''literally, "[[sea]] [[lion]]"'') [[sea lion]] (''eared'')
*[[해구]] ([[海狗]], ''haegu'') (''literally, "[[sea]] [[dog]]" cf. German [[Seehund]] (as if a literal translation)'') [[fur]] [[seal]] (''eared'') 
*[[수달]] ([[水獺]], ''sudal'') (''literally, "[[water]] [[otter]]". Both English words are cognate, hence a tautologic Sino-Korean as usual.'') [[otter]]

====Antonyms====
*[[물범]] (''mulbeom'') (''literally, "[[water]] [[tiger]]"'') [[hair]] [[seal]] (''earless'') 
*[[바다표범]] (''bada-pyobeom'') (''literally, "[[sea]] [[leopard]]"'') [[hair]] [[seal]] (''earless'') 
*[[해표]] ([[海豹]], ''haepyo'') (''literally, "[[sea]] [[leopard]]"'') [[hair]] [[seal]] (''earless'')

====See also====
*[[바다코끼리]] (''bada-kokkiri'') (''literally, "sea elephant"'') [[sea elephant]], [[elephant seal]], [[walrus]], [[sea horse]] (''mammal'') 
*[[해상]] ([[海象]], ''haesang'') (''literally, "sea elephant"'') [[sea elephant]], [[elephant seal]], [[walrus]], [[sea horse]] (''mammal'') 
*[[해마]] ([[海馬]], ''haema'') (''literally, "sea horse"'')  [[sea horse]] (''mammal''), [[sea elephant]], [[elephant seal]], [[walrus]] (''allegedly from inversion of Old Norse [[hrosshvalr]], "horse-whale"'')
 
